claim(address).details: Transfers ownership of the reverse CNS record associated with the      calling account.

params.owner: The address to set as the owner of the reverse record in CNS.

returns._0: The CNS node hash of the reverse record.

claimWithResolver(address,address).details: Transfers ownership of the reverse CNS record associated with the      calling account.

params.owner: The address to set as the owner of the reverse record in CNS.
params.resolver: The address of the resolver to set; 0 to leave unchanged.

returns._0: The CNS node hash of the reverse record.

params.ensAddr: The address of the CNS registry.
params.resolverAddr: The address of the default reverse resolver.

node(address).details: Returns the node hash for a given account's reverse records.

setName(string).details: Sets the `name()` record for the reverse CNS record associated with the calling account. First updates the resolver to the default reverse resolver if necessary.

params._name: The name to set for this address.

returns._0: The CNS node hash of the reverse record.
